The paper deals with motion planning for multiple robots (discs) in a geometric environment (simple polygon), which suggests that it belongs to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The problem involves geometric computations and algorithms, which is a characteristic of Computational Geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the use of data structures to efficiently solve the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The problem involves optimization and decision-making, which are characteristics of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories.
